From 26502a96fefe3e675e4de60a18abbc74a8e4faff Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:29:25 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 01/16] test(agentic): add production-path payout judge
 evaluation
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

P-JUDGE replaces the copied-logic live harness with an eval that invokes the EXACT
production judgment path — no duplicated prompt, parsing, confidence rule, injection
handling, or autopay logic that could drift. `runJudgeEval` calls the real
`verifySubmission` and reaches the decision through the real `gateFromBrief`;
judge-eval-gate.test.ts proves the eval's classification IS that production gate.

- brain.ts gains a behavior-preserving DI seam (`VerifyOptions` provider/fallback/fetchImpl
  + `providerForModel`). A plain `verifySubmission(input)` is byte-identical to before, so
  the frozen judgment layer is unchanged; the live red-team was re-run (15/15 held, control
  paid) to re-verify jailbreak resistance after touching the frozen file.
- Per-row provenance: fixture id/category, requested vs ACTUAL model, primary/fallback,
  prompt version, final decision, autopay-qualified, a decision hash (non-sensitive, never
  raw content), latency/cost, parse/refusal/timeout status.
- Metrics separate the catastrophic wrong-autopay (hard stop) from honest-autopay,
  false-hold, provenance faults, and variance; genuine-but-weak evidence SHOULD review, so
  it is not counted as an expected autopay. A DOCUMENTED, deferred known-gap (the entailment
  veto) is tracked + reported, not a hard stop until the fix lands.
- judge-fault-injection.test.ts drives the real chain under simulated timeout / refusal /
  malformed / empty / 500 → heuristic (never autopays), and a primary outage → the fallback
  provider with correct provenance. The old copied `scripts/judge-eval.mjs` is removed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
