From 83afd73e18ee3a54af18cc1319b9c960ebccd854 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:29:53 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 02/16] feat(deputy): add shadow-gated rendered evidence
 capture
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A client-rendered SPA returns a near-empty shell to the static evidence fetch, so genuine
work HOLDS for lack of visible text. A guarded headless browser recovers the rendered
innerText the tester actually saw — the largest fix for genuine URL-lane evidence.

Because this is a NON-MONOTONIC capture change (it can turn a hold into a pay), it ships as a
true three-state rollout `RENDERED_EVIDENCE_MODE=off|shadow|enforce`:
  · off (default; unknown value → off): the renderer is never invoked, static path unchanged.
  · shadow (legacy RENDERED_EVIDENCE=1 maps here, never enforce): the renderer runs and a
    static-vs-rendered comparison is recorded, but the JUDGE STILL SEES STATIC — payout is
    byte-for-byte unchanged.
  · enforce: rendered text may reach the judge, only when strictly richer.
Rendered text that reaches a model is returned as EvidenceResult.text, so it gets the exact
same untrusted markers, caps, sanitization, and truncation as static.

Security (the evidence URL is attacker-controlled, its JS executes in our browser): every
request re-validates against the frozen requestGuard + a public-host DNS check (verbatim from
the Field Test), downloads + popups are refused, the context is ephemeral, hard time caps,
and it does not rely on networkidle alone (a bounded settle handles never-idle SPAs). Any
failure preserves the static result. Structured provenance carries lengths + digests +
outcome only — never raw page text — so it is safe to journal. Playwright is a lazy import so
evidence.ts pulls no browser deps unless a render fires. Verified: excalidraw.com static 10
chars → rendered 430 chars.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
