From f93a0fd52f5588023e5076ed0e68043f71f815ea Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 20:30:23 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 03/16] fix(deputy): block autopay from unapproved judge models
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

An autopay could previously be authorized by ANY engine-"llm" brief — including one from the
fallback provider (deepseek), which never passed the promotion battery. Closes that hole with
a deterministic, versioned autopay-approved-model policy (model-policy.ts), checked in the
pipeline AFTER the autopilot gate:

  · the ACTUAL model that produced the brief (brief.model, stamped by callProvider — not the
    requested env var) must be on the approved allowlist;
  · a fallback model, an alias that resolved to a different model, or missing provenance →
    MANUAL REVIEW, even at pay/1.0;
  · an unapproved model can NEVER authorize a payout.

The existing evidence + money gates are untouched — this only ever turns a would-pay into a
hold (subtract-only, cannot cause a wrong payout). It is deterministic pipeline code, never a
prompt, and journals `judge_model_unapproved` with the requested + actual model identity.

The allowlist seeds the current prod primary (google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite-preview) and the
P-JUDGE-passed anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5, so the DEPLOYED model's behavior is unchanged;
adding a model requires re-running P-JUDGE (>=3 runs) + the live red-team for it. Pipeline test
fixtures updated to the canonical approved model (they exercise the autopay path), plus two new
integration tests: an unapproved model and a null-provenance model with perfect qualifying
briefs both HOLD (judge_model_unapproved), never broadcast.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
