- probes cannot ride the mission snapshot without persistence — CODE-CONFIRMED (attach maps
  fields explicitly; payout reads the persisted row) → probes stay shadow/demo-only until a
  durable, digest-bound verification contract exists;
- "subtract-only" was imprecise: NEW verifier checks are subtract-only, but model/capture
  changes are NON-MONOTONIC and require shadow → promotion criteria → rollback flags;
- an unproven model (incl. the fallback) may not autopay — review-only until it passes the
  battery;
- replay proves "independently reproducible", not "this tester did it";
- the entailment check is a semantic model VETO, not positive deterministic verification;
- cut testerPhrasings and the arbitrary $5→4-source rule; probe error taxonomy + backpressure;
- P-JUDGE is the bigger battery with corrected metrics (wrong-autopay = catastrophic; genuine
  work is not required to autopay).

