From b979b1fc9af0821d7aa929526dd74c20b7db8584 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 21:39:55 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 05/16] test(agentic): correct payout promotion accounting
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

A known-gap wrong-autopay is a SUBSET of the catastrophic total, never removed from
it. The earlier P-JUDGE accounting carved the quote-present-non-entailing 1/3 autopay
out of the wrong-autopay total and could then print "0 wrong-autopay" while a
non-entailing fixture had in fact autopaid. That is the exact laundering this closes.

judgeMetricsFrom (extracted, pure, unit-tested without an LLM) now reports:
  - wrongAutopayTotal      — EVERY autopay of a non-permitted fixture (the zero-tolerance number)
  - knownGapWrongAutopays  — the documented-deferred SUBSET (tracked, never subtracted)
  - unexpectedWrongAutopays — surprise wrong-autopays (a hard test failure)
  - providerFailures / conclusive — infra-invalid rows (heuristic fallback, rate-limit,
    provenance fault) are NOT model-quality evidence and make a run inconclusive
  - promotionEligible = wrongAutopayTotal===0 && provenanceViolations===0 && conclusive
A known-gap autopay keeps promotionEligible=false — it is reported, never excused.

The live battery drives the REAL verifySubmission + gateFromBrief with a bounded retry
so a transient rate-limit degrades to "inconclusive", not a false green. judge-accounting
proves the rules on synthetic rows; judge-eval.live asserts unexpectedWrongAutopays===0
and intact provenance as the promotion hard-stops.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
