From 145dbb2baed364ab371899791dbbf9f4a58445b5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 22:04:42 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 07/16] fix(deputy): reject repaired or incomplete money
 decisions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The payout path parsed model output with parseBriefContent(repairJson(content)) — the
tolerant repair salvaged fenced, prose-wrapped, brace-dropped, trailing-garbage, and even
TRUNCATED bodies into a "decision" that could then autopay. A model cut off at max_tokens,
or a provider that ignored response_format, could yield a partial PAY brief and move real
money.

callProvider now uses a STRICT money parse (parseMoneyBrief): JSON.parse only — no
repairJson, fence-strip, brace re-wrap, balanced-object extraction, or partial completion.
It also inspects the completion envelope and fails closed on an abnormal finish_reason
(length/max_tokens/content_filter/tool_calls) or an explicit refusal, and requires the
money-critical fields (recommendation + a numeric confidence) to be explicitly present.
Any deviation → the caller fails over → the heuristic, which can never autopay.

The strict parse is a strict SUBSET of what repair accepted, so it can only REDUCE autopay
recall, never increase autopay. The tolerant repairJson is untouched and preserved for the
non-money generation paths (src/lib/llm/complete.ts has its own). PARSER_POLICY_VERSION
bumps to payout-parse-v2 and the approved identities move to v2 (the strict parser is a
subset of the evaluated v1 on the money path, so approval carries; confirmed by the new
deterministic battery + the live red-team re-run).

brain-strict-parse.test.ts (13 cases, no network) proves: clean strict JSON with or without
a finish_reason still parses (recall preserved); fenced / dropped-braces / prose-wrapped /
trailing-garbage / truncated±marker / content_filter / refusal / missing-confidence /
missing-recommendation all fail closed and never autopay; and a repairable PAY body the old
path would have salvaged + autopaid is now rejected to the heuristic.

Live full P-JUDGE re-run was provider-rate-limited (HTTP 429) in this environment; the
bounded retry correctly degraded to inconclusive (heuristic), and the 429s occur before any
parse, so they are unrelated to the strict parser. Not deployed, not enforced.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
