From b8b4950ff094855b873d0105a055de3734bf2ce8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 22:17:05 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 08/16] feat(deputy): add shadow-gated criterion entailment
 veto
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes the §5.8 entailment gap: a brief can mark a criterion "met" on a quote that merely
MENTIONS a thing without PROVING the tester did it — e.g. "Single Sign-On (SSO)" in a
marketing feature list quoted for a criterion that required actually logging in with SSO —
and the autopilot gate then autopays. The new veto is the last line before autopay: an
INDEPENDENTLY-APPROVED model re-checks whether the brief's OWN cited quotes ENTAIL each met
criterion, and can only ever downgrade a would-be autopay to manual review.

  - src/lib/deputy/entailment.ts — the subsystem. ENTAILMENT_MODE=off|shadow|enforce
    (default off; any unknown value → off; only exact "enforce" changes a payout). Runs
    ONLY post-qualification (after the autopilot + identity gates would authorize autopay).
    STRICT structured output {results:[{criterionId,verdict,reasonCode,reason}]} with NO
    repair (JSON.parse only), deterministic validation (exactly one row per requested id,
    verdict enum, normal finish, no refusal), untrusted note/quote inside markers, and a
    separate ENTAILMENT_APPROVED_MODELS allowlist (approving a judge model does NOT approve
    it to veto). Fails CLOSED (vetoes) on missing provider / unapproved model / provider
    error / abnormal finish / invalid output. Never throws; never mutates the brief.
  - pipeline b3 — off skips; shadow runs + journals verdict enums + digests (never raw
    content) and leaves the payout unchanged; enforce downgrades a not_entailed/uncertain/
    failure to a held "entailment_veto". Placed inside the url-verifiable !isObservation
    block, after the identity gate.

Proofs: entailment.test.ts (25 cases) — strict validation (fenced/trailing/short/long/dup/
unknown-id/bad-enum all reject), fail-closed veto semantics, mode parsing, brief→input
mapping, independent approval. pipeline.test.ts mode truth table — off/shadow never change
the payout; only enforce holds. entailment-eval.live.ts — the live semantic battery (14
mention-only vs proving fixtures) asserting a mention-only quote is always vetoed; runnable
under ENTAIL_EVAL=1, currently provider-rate-limited like P-JUDGE.

Enforce is NOT enabled (default off). Not deployed.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
