From fd4771067e5a9f0744c7c0582a047b1182548d97 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 23:24:56 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 11/16] fix(deputy): require explicit normal completion for
 money decisions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Gate B admitted a money decision whenever the body parsed, treating an ABSENT finish_reason
as acceptable (a deny-list of known-abnormal reasons). That violates fail-closed: a
truncated response (finish_reason "length"/"max_tokens") can still carry a syntactically
complete PAY object, and a provider that omits the metadata would silently pass.

A new completion adapter (completion.ts) preserves the provider's actual termination metadata
and the money path now requires an EXPLICIT recognized normal completion (allow-list = {stop}
for the OpenAI-compatible route). A refusal, an absent finish_reason, a truncation, a content
filter, or any unknown reason fails closed to the heuristic — even if the JSON parses. The
money path never infers a normal completion from a parseable object. The rule is enforced in
callProvider, so it applies INDEPENDENTLY to the primary and the fallback (both go through it).
Adding another normal marker (e.g. a gateway that normalizes to "end_turn") requires a verified
live observation, never a speculative widening. The entailment veto's own completion is aligned
to the same adapter (an abnormal/absent finish → veto, the safe direction).

This is strictly a SUBSET of what v2 accepted, so it can only reduce autopay recall, never
increase autopay. PARSER_POLICY_VERSION bumps payout-parse-v2 → v3 (the money-admission policy
changed), so the identity requires re-evaluation.

