From 49c2b36c1e5af52439f809e1d60a0f69437078ba Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Wed, 22 Jul 2026 23:35:41 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 12/16] fix(deputy): keep unevaluated policy identities
 unapproved
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Gate B (as amended in C2) had payout-parse-v3 sitting in the approved set to preserve recall.
That self-approves a combination that never completed a conclusive live promotion. This
separates CANDIDATE from APPROVED and empties the production approved registry.

  - CANDIDATE_IDENTITIES lists the combinations present in the code / configured for prod
    (gemini-flash-lite and haiku on commonstack, payout-v1, payout-parse-v3). They authorize
    nothing.
  - PRODUCTION_APPROVED is EMPTY. No (provider, model, prompt, parser) combination has a clean
    conclusive promotion run (the live P-JUDGE/P-ENTAIL are gateway rate-limited → inconclusive).
    An ApprovalRecord (provider, model, promptVersion, parserVersion, evalSuite digest, approvedOn,
    evidence) is required to promote a candidate — a deliberate code change, never env-driven.
  - isApprovedJudgeIdentity checks the prod registry (empty) plus a TEST-ONLY overlay populated
    only by __approveForTest/__clearTestApprovals (no production caller). So tests inject an
    approved identity EXPLICITLY; they never rely on a shipped default.

Consequence: with the shipped registry, every url-verifiable autopay safely falls to MANUAL
REVIEW — deploying an unapproved identity produces review, not a payout. A new pipeline test
proves this end to end (empty registry → held with judge_identity_unapproved, never settled),
and the pay-path suites now register the fixture identity explicitly.

Wording for the record: nothing here is deployed, so the running production code is still the
pre-Gate-A version. The configured production MODEL is not the same as the payout-parse-v3
IDENTITY being production-approved — it is not. MODEL_POLICY_VERSION → autopay-policy-v2.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
