MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The Gate-B redirect fix guarded redirects at the Playwright route layer, which still leaves a
TOCTOU / DNS-rebinding window: a Node preflight resolves a host public, then Chromium re-resolves
and connects itself, and the route layer never sees WebSockets or every subresource. This
replaces per-request page-level guarding with ONE authoritative egress boundary.

  - src/lib/net/ip-classify.ts — allow-only-global-unicast IP classification (via ipaddr.js, now a
    declared direct dep): loopback, private, CGNAT, link-local (incl. 169.254.169.254), multicast,
    broadcast, reserved/doc/benchmark, IPv6 ULA, and every transition range that can embed a private
    IPv4 (6to4/NAT64/Teredo) are refused; IPv4-mapped IPv6 re-classifies by its embedded v4; hex/
    integer/octal IPv4 literals canonicalize; fails closed on parse error.
  - src/lib/net/egress-proxy.ts — a guarded local forward/CONNECT proxy. Chromium launches with
    `proxy` + `--proxy-bypass-list=<-loopback>`, so EVERY request (nav, redirect hop, subresource,
    WebSocket, worker, beacon) exits through it. The proxy resolves each host itself, requires every
    resolved address to be public (mixed-record defense), PINS the validated IP and connects to
    exactly it (preserving Host/SNI) — closing the rebinding window — enforces approved ports
    (80/443) + read-only methods over HTTP, bounds bytes/time/concurrency, force-closes sockets on
    shutdown, and fails closed.
  - evidence-render.ts + field-test.ts (the only two Playwright callers; env.ts is config-only) both
    launch through the proxy. The redundant manual redirect-follow is gone — the proxy re-validates
    each hop.

Proofs (internal fixture receives ZERO requests in every attack): ip-classify.test (full attack
set), egress-proxy.test (12 direct: private literal, metadata, weird encodings, mapped-loopback,
hostname→loopback, mixed records, rebinding-pin, bad port, state-changing method, non-http, CONNECT
to private, positive forward), evidence-render.browser.test (15 real-browser through the proxy:
private subresource, redirect-to-private, redirect chain, DNS-rebinding, WebSocket-to-internal,
popup/download/SW/hang/reset/cap + no process leak), field-test integration (39, through the proxy).
Threat model + architecture: docs/egress-boundary.md.

RENDERED_EVIDENCE_MODE stays off and shadow stays prohibited for untrusted URLs until reviewed.
Residual (documented): HTTPS method filtering is impossible at a CONNECT proxy; the destination
guard is the operative SSRF defense there. Not deployed.

