From 1ed381932436502f9acd99eda97ac792acf587b2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:03:02 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 14/16] test(agentic): make promotion evaluations resumable
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The live P-JUDGE / P-ENTAIL runs to date ground a loop against a throttled account and could
report a "green" that was really 57/57 rate-limited heuristic rows. This adds a resumable,
rate-limit-honest promotion runner so a promotion decision rests on the REQUIRED number of
VALID responses from the actual candidate model — never rate-limited, heuristic-fallback, or
transport-failed rows.

  - src/lib/deputy/promotion-runner.ts — pure orchestrator (clock, sleep, RNG, per-call worker,
    checkpoint store all injected). Starts with a one-request QUOTA PROBE and stops immediately
    on a 429, reporting the earliest safe retry (Retry-After) — it never grinds a throttled
    account. Then: concurrency 1, a configurable minimum interval, bounded exponential backoff
    with full jitter honoring Retry-After, a hard request + cost budget, a checkpoint written
    after every answered slot, and --resume that skips recorded slots. It NEVER retries a
    semantically-valid model response (a real decision — even a "bad" one — is a data point, not
    a retry); only 429/transport failures back off. Status is conclusive | quota_blocked |
    budget_exhausted | incomplete — only conclusive is promotion evidence.
  - promotion-runner.test.ts — 10 deterministic cases (no network/real time): valid→conclusive,
    quota-probe-429 stops with no further calls, later-429 retried with Retry-After, model_failure
    answered-but-not-counted-and-not-retried, bounded-retry→incomplete, request + cost budgets,
    resume-skips-done, checkpoint-after-each, min-interval pacing.
  - promotion-eval.live.ts — wires the runner to the REAL verifySubmission / entailment veto with
    a status-capturing fetch (to tell a 429 from a model failure) + a JSON checkpoint file; a
    conclusive judge run computes judgeMetricsFrom and asserts 0 unexpected wrong-autopay. A
    quota-blocked / incomplete run is reported, never a false green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
