From 8f54295f0ac9de6fea7b062e14b02c5f1ed14ee4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sage Builder <bc230212964ssh@vu.edu.pk>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 01:03:02 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 15/16] test: eliminate shared-resource contention
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Root cause of the observed pipeline-identity flake ("a CONSISTENT campaign still settles",
failed at 5008ms in one full-suite run, passed in isolation): NOT a shared-resource bug. The
test is deterministic (it mocks verifySubmission + verifyEvidence, so no LLM/network) and
isolated (vitest's forks pool gives each file its own process → own process.env → own in-memory
SQLite). It was a TIMEOUT under CPU starvation — a CPU/network-heavy background live-eval process
was running concurrently, starving the worker so a DB-seeding + crypto-hashing + full-pipeline
test crept past the tight 5s default. Confirmed: the test passes 20/20 in isolation; the full
suite passes 3/3 consecutively; the browser security suite passes 3/3.

  - vitest.config.ts — pin the isolation explicitly (pool: "forks", isolate: true) so per-file
    process isolation can never silently regress to a shared-context pool, and raise testTimeout /
    hookTimeout to 15s. That is headroom for real DB/crypto/browser work under scheduler contention
    — a GENUINE hang (unresolved promise) still fails, so it is headroom, not retry-based hiding.
  - package.json — dedicated release commands so the heavyweight security suites cannot be silently
    omitted from a checklist: `test:browser-security` (renderer + egress proxy + IP classifier) and
    `test:field-egress` (the Field Test through the proxy).

Operational note: do not run CPU/network-heavy processes (e.g. a live promotion eval) concurrently
with the vitest suite.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
